Author: ashiapmanman
Content: the firebird is originally a ballet by the russian composer igor stravinsky., released in 1910. i like to call this as the first trilogy of his early ballets. stravinsky actually worked on another ballet project titled "petrushka", which he then promptly finished and premiered next year in 1911. after the massive success of both of those ballets, he composed another ballet with the name "the rite of spring". the rite of spring is famous for its stupidly many time signature changes and contemporary (_at the time_) composition style.

Author: ashiapmanman
Content: petrushka is known (outside of the classical world) for its petrushka chord, a c major triad and an f# major triad played at the same time.

Author: ekast237707
Content:
English Lyrics

I'm connecting together and drawing mosaic pieces one by one
As well as the encounter and parting you gave me

I think, "It shouldn't be like this," and go to sleep
And when I awaken, it's the same old unchanging, fruitless effort
I repeat it meaninglessly

I picked up and gathered the mosaic pieces for "a way to live a good life"
That warped thing seemed beautiful to me
Above the path I chose to the end while I bluffed, while I failed
The pieces came unstuck and fell, and I would not bury them

A world spread all over every will
Even though I must have something I can't yield to anyone
I'm worried about the multiple colors

While bewitched by the various colors and shapes in the mosaic pieces
I wished far too much for "youthful indiscretion"
Believing in the cement of love in the gaps in my heart, I washed down
Pieces that will never, ever melt together

Because contrast is beautiful, roughness conversely works well
For some reason, I won't wait for my turn and find my own style of answer

The mosaic pieces brilliantly project the lies and mistakes of my past
The more I think I want to erase them all
The more I still can't advance past the start line there when I turn around
I'll try picking up and gathering my dreams once more
I'm connecting together and drawing mosaic pieces one by one
As well as the encounter and parting you gave me

Author: fingeredemption
Content:
Intestine Baalism - An Anatomy of the Beast

Intestine Baalism were one of the first significant death metal band to ever come out of Japan, and they sound more like something that came straight out of Sweden. It really is the product of Dismember and Entombed influence where most of the album is just straight up old school death metal, even the melodic part of the album feels very ‚Äúdark‚Äù compared to the majority of the melodeath scene where they lean towards very happy sounding leads. The memorable leads everyone is talking about just happened to he smacked right in the middle or at the end of every track (which is actually the typical Japanese-style music), but oh my GOD once you finished it, you want to listen to it over and over again for that ASTONISHING guitar works. Like holy shit it‚Äôs straight out of a very dramatic boss fight finale or a finale to a very peak anime if you would like to put it that way, especially the B-side of this album which is THE PEAKEST OF PEAK A MELODIC DEATH METAL ALBUM CAN EVER BE!!!!

Seriously, listen to it.
